#!/bin/bash
host=$1
localport=$2
remoteport=$3
target=$4
direction=${5:-"L"}
socfile="/tmp/.sshtunnel.$host.$localport.$remoteport.$target"
if [ ! -e "$socfile" ]; then
	ssh -4 -$direction "$localport:$target:$remoteport" "$host" -f -N -M -S "$socfile"
else
	ssh -S "$socfile" -O exit "$target" 
fi

